â˜ï¸ Amazon S3 (Simple Storage Service)
Definition: A scalable, secure, and durable cloud storage service by AWS.

Purpose: Store and retrieve unlimited data from anywhere on the web.

Use Cases: Backup, archiving, website content hosting, big data analytics, disaster recovery.

ğŸª£ S3 Buckets
What They Are: Containers (like top-level folders) that hold objects (files).

Naming Rules: Globally unique, 3â€“63 characters, lowercase letters/numbers/periods/hyphens, DNS-compliant.

Region Selection: Impacts latency, cost, and compliance requirements.

ğŸ¯ Why Use S3 Buckets
Durability & Availability: 99.999999999% durability (11 nines).

Scalability: No capacity limits.

Security: Encryption, IAM policies, bucket policies, audit logging.

Performance: Optimized for high throughput.

Cost-Effective: Multiple storage classes (Standard, Infrequent Access, Glacier, etc.).

âš™ï¸ Key Features
Versioning: Keep multiple versions of objects to prevent accidental overwrites/deletes.

Bucket Policies & IAM: Fine-grained access control.

Object Metadata: Content type, cache control, encryption, custom tags.

Encryption: SSE-S3 (AWS keys), SSE-KMS (customer-managed keys), SSE-C (customer-provided).

Lifecycle Management: Automate transitions (e.g., move to Glacier after 30 days).

Multipart Uploads: Upload large files in parts for speed and resiliency.

Batch Operations: Perform bulk actions (copy, tag, restore) across millions of objects.

ğŸš€ Advanced Features
Storage Classes: Standard, Intelligent-Tiering, One Zone-IA, Glacier, Glacier Deep Archive.

Replication:

CRR (Cross-Region Replication) â†’ disaster recovery, compliance.

SRR (Same-Region Replication) â†’ resilience, low-latency access.

Event Notifications: Trigger Lambda, SQS, or SNS when objects are created/deleted.

Monitoring: CloudWatch metrics, access logging, CloudTrail auditing.

ğŸ” Security & Compliance
Encryption at Rest & Transit: Protect data with SSE and SSL/TLS.

Access Logging: Track requests for auditing.

IAM Roles & Policies: Control access securely.

Bucket Policies: JSON-based rules for permissions.

ğŸ› ï¸ Management & Troubleshooting
Tools: AWS Console, CLI, SDKs, APIs.

Common Errors:

Access Denied: Check IAM/bucket policies.

Bucket Not Found: Verify name/region.

Quota Exceeded: Review storage limits or request increase.

Recovery: Enable versioning or replication to restore deleted objects.

